
[1]criterion

   CRITERION, n. plu. [Gr., to judge. See Crime.] A standard of judging;
   any established law, rule, principle or fact, by which facts,
   propositions and opinions are compared, in order to discover their
   truth or falsehood, or by which a correct judgment may be formed.
